      • onProductCancel

        public void onProductCancel​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
                     throws java.io.IOException

        Parameters:
        actionEvent - The cancel button is clicked.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • onProductsSave

        public void onProductsSave​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
                    throws java.io.IOException
        This method will save a new product to the inventory system. This method will save a new product, the inventory stock field must be between min and max, and max must be greater than min. It will not allow the user to save if any fields are empty or have incorrect input. The new product will be saved with any associated parts added to the 'associated parts' table.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - The save button is clicked.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • searchAddProductTable

        public void searchAddProductTable​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        This method will search the 'parts' table on the 'Add Product' screen. This method will allow the user to search and filter the 'parts' table by part ID or part name. If the user is searching by part ID, the corresponding part will be highlighted. If the user is searching by part name, the corresponding part(s) will be filtered.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - The search field is entered.

      • toAddPart

        public void toAddPart​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        This method will add a selected part from the 'parts' table to the 'associated parts' table.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - The add button is clicked.

      • toRemoveAssociatedPart

        public void toRemoveAssociatedPart​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)

        Parameters:
        actionEvent - The remove button is clicked.

      • initialize

        public void initialize​(java.net.URL url,
                       java.util.ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
        This is the initialize method for the Add Product Form. The ID field will be initialized with an auto-generated ID number and the top part's table will contain the parts inventory.
